<reference id="enum_rendermodetype">
    <title><ph keyref="RENDER_MODE_TYPE"/></title>
    <shortdesc id="short"><ph id="shortdesc">Video display modes.</ph></shortdesc>
    <refbody>
        <section id="parameters">
            <title>Enumerator</title>
            <parml>
            <plentry>
                <pt><ph keyref="RENDER_MODE_HIDDEN"/></pt>
                <pd>1: Uniformly scale the video until one of its dimension fits the boundary (zoomed to fit).  The window is filled. One dimension of the video might have clipped contents.</pd>
            </plentry>
            </parml>
            <parml>
            <plentry>
                <pt><ph keyref="RENDER_MODE_FIT"/></pt>
                <pd>2: Uniformly scale the video until one of its dimension fits the boundary (zoomed to fit). Priority is to ensuring that all video content is displayed. Areas that are not filled due to disparity in the aspect ratio are filled with black.</pd>
            </plentry>
            </parml>
            <parml>
            <plentry props="cpp android flutter">
                <pt><ph keyref="RENDER_MODE_ADAPTIVE"/></pt>
                <pd>
                    <dl outputclass="deprecated">
                    <dlentry>
                        <dt>Deprecated:</dt>
                        <dd>3: This mode is deprecated.</dd>
                    </dlentry>
                    </dl>
                </pd>
            </plentry>
            </parml> </section>
    </refbody>
